An Act establishing a tax credit for individuals paying for home health care and hospice.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 (1) A taxpayer who pays for direct home health services from a home care provider
2 licensed with the Massachusetts Department of Public Health, or the Center for Medicare and
3 Medicaid Services or certified with the Massachusetts Department of Occupational Safety, for
4 the care of an elderly parent or in-law 60 years of age or older who resides in the commonwealth
5 shall be allowed a deduction of $5000.
6 (2) A taxpayer who pays for his own home health care services from a home health care
7 provider licensed with the Massachusetts Department of Public Health, or the Center for
8 Medicare and Medicaid Services or certified with the Massachusetts Department of Occupational
9 Safety shall be allowed a deduction of $5000.
1 of 2

10 (3) A taxpayer who pays for direct home hospice services for themselves or another from
11 a home health care provider licensed with the Massachusetts Department of Public Health, or the
12 Center for Medicare and Medicaid Services or certified with the Massachusetts Department of
13 Occupational Safety shall be allowed a deduction of $5000.
